cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces an extended propositional interaction logic and investigates its first-order level as a formal language for the interactions of parametric systems.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses component-based design and architecture modelling, which are important topics in software engineering.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper deals with formal modelling of systems, which is related to programming language semantics.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses formal modelling of systems, which is a topic that can be relevant to AI applications.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with modelling large systems and their interactions, which can be relevant to distributed and parallel computing.
